<dl id="n36029b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36029b">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36029b"> 29(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Tolboth St</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Just outside the church in Parliament Square, the supposed grave of John Knox is indicated by a stone set in the pavement bearing his initials, and in the pavement to the west a heart indicates the site of the <mark>old Tolbooth</mark>, which figures prominently in Scott&apos;s <cite>Heart of Midlothian</cite>. <small> &ldquo;EDINBURGH&rdquo; <a name="EBED" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBED"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 938c</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
